descript.abstract:
This dataset represents the Albemarle County Police response areas.  The response areas are divided up into beats, sectors, and districts.
***Notes from the changes in 2004*** The sectors were changed from their previous configuration based largely on the police department's desire to: allow for and promote a five-minute response time to all emergency calls for service in identified development areas; attempt to equalize the workload in beat areas; reduce the number of calls to which officers respond outside of their beats; provide areas that can reasonably be patrolled by a single patrol vehicle; and create boundaries that take into consideration various factors like county-owned facilities, roadway and geographic constraints, and future growth.
The Town of Scottsville is given a separate beat designation (21) only because it is sometimes patrolled by its own law enforcement agency and this separate beat designation allows for better data analysis.
descript.purpose: This dataset is intended to show where the police response areas are in Albemarle County.
